               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371023-name-301" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-301" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-301" type="surname" value="BURROWS"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-301" type="given" value="SAMUEL"></interp>SAMUEL BURROWS</persName>
                  </hi>. I keep the White Swan, in Ray-street, Clerkenwell I received information on the 30th of September, and ran after the prisoner I overtook him, and said, Give me that pot you have got—he said, I have got no pot"—I said, You have—he then said he would give it me if I would let him go—I said I would not—he then said he would give me half-a-crown to let him go—I brought him back, and the officer took him—the pot belongs to Mr. Grinham, who serves the same factory that I do, and it was in my house when taken.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371023-name-302" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-302" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-302" type="surname" value="KING"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18371023-name-302" type="given" value="AMY"></interp>AMY KING</persName>
                  </hi>. The prisoner came and asked for a glass of porter, and I served him—this pot was safe then, and when he was gone it was missed—no one else went in.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18371023-name-303" type="witnessName">
